&lt;p&gt;Whether serving ultra-traditional sushi or cutting-edge Japanese dishes with Brazilian influence, Kinoshita specializes in Kappo Cuisine, a combination of Japanese haute cuisine and interaction between chef and guests. With experience in Tokyo, Barcelona and New York, Chef Murakami established Kinoshita in S&atilde;o Paulo, which has the largest Japanese community outside of Japan. Kinoshita is named &lt;strong&gt;The Daily Meal 2014 #2 Restaurant&lt;/strong&gt; in Brazil. Handicap accessible. Smart casual attire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please book by contacting Kinoshita by phone at +55 11 3849 6940&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mention Diners Club International Privileges Dining Collection to receive your special benefit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide your name, date you would like to dine, number of guests, preferred time, cell or local (hotel) phone number&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cancellation Policy: as a courtesy, Kinoshita asks that reservations be cancelled at least 24 hours in advance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TERMS &amp;amp; CONDITIONS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow booking instructions to ensure receiving your Privileges Dining Collection amenity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Based on availability at the time of booking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A main course must be purchased to receive your dining benefit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your Privileges Dining Collection benefit may not be combined with other offers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fulfillment of the offer is the sole responsibility of the participating&nbsp;Diners Club International&nbsp;Restaurant&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Restaurant participation and benefits are subject to change or cancellation without notice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

